 Register Today  for GasMart/Power 2002
March 18-20, 2002
Reno, NV


 


Look Who's Talking...

Keynote Address: State of the Market 
Executive Vice President & Chief Operating Officer, Duke Energy North America, Richard Sherrill will assess the current state of the wholesale natural gas and power markets, and offer scenarios going forward. 

AND . . .Hear from Energy Information Administration (EIA) experts on their plans for the about-to-be-launched replacement to American Gas Association's natural gas storage survey. In a special session Wednesday, March 20 EIA Senior Analyst Roy Kass will discuss progress on the new weekly storage report, as well as other products the Energy Department agency provides to inform the market. EIA representatives also will be available to discuss their products and take questions at their Showcase space. 

In other sessions, hear from industry leaders: Veteran Analyst Ben Schlesinger... Dynegy Vice President Peter Esposito... Williams EM&T President Bill Hobbs... TXU Vice President Jeff Shorter... Futures analyst Cynthia Kase... Sr. VP Calpine Jim Macias... Poten Partners' Gordon Shearer... Anadarko's Richard Sharples... Plus representatives of the California Energy Commission, SoCal Gas, the Western Power Trading Forum, the Cal-ISO and FERC, among others. 

They will be talking about: 

                    -The Impact of Enron and 9/11 on the energy industry 
                    -Assessing the Winter: Industry & System Performance 
                    -What's Ahead for Power Generation 
                    -Security Issues & Costs 
                    -New LNG & Arctic Gas Supplies 
                    -How to Survive in E&P 
                    -RTOs and Market Mitigation (Price Caps) 
                    -Natural Gas Infrastructure and 'Reserve Margin' for the California Market 
                    -Factoring the Weather into your Energy Plan 




EXHIBIT - become an integral part of our new Showcase format , moving beyond a trade fair to an integrated event, emphasizing networking within the innovative floor displays. Showcasers include: Allegro Development, Duke Energy, FIMAT USA, Gulfstream Natural Gas System, KWI, Morgan Stanley, Reliant Energy Services, Williams Energy Services. Click here  to see a Floorplan and a complete list of Showcasers. 


